properties.name: Person Match Flow
properties.documentation: Process to match CP, NCP, child from an external referral source (IBES, CSNET, FACS, etc) to the Hub and Child Support application.  Purpose: To prevent creation of duplicate clients.

properties.name: Start Client Match
properties.documentation: Receive data from Interface source (IBES, FACS, CSNET) and begin Matching Clients included in the referral.

properties.name: Match CP Client
properties.documentation:
Look for client in different systems (CS, IBES and ICARE), return Client Found, if not client found, continue flow. 

If Match returns more than 1 result, then present resolution task to user. 
If Match returns 1 result, then consider match and move to next step in flow. 
If 0 match returned, then No match found, move to next step in flow.

properties.name: Resolve Applicant
properties.documentation: This task automatically sets when Nexi is unable to add a new customer or match the requesting person’s information to an existing customer. SRSs review the information received from IBES to determine whether to add a new customer or match the customer to an existing customer.

properties.name: Create New CP Client
properties.documentation: Creates a new client via the WS call and sets the CP_CONTACT_UPDATE variable to true.

properties.name: CP Client Created
properties.documentation: When a Client is matched to one and only one Child Support ClientID.

The outcome the CS User selects when resolving a Match Person issue.  Outcomes include:
-Create a New Client
-Selecting one option presented by the system (Results in Match Client)
-Searching for an existing Child Support Client and selecting that client (Results in Match Client.)

properties.name: Existing CS Client  Matched
properties.documentation: Indicating that a single CS client was matched based on the CIN Match rules.

properties.name: Check For Duplicate CP
properties.documentation: Checks if the CP is already known to Child Support

properties.text: Pull back all known 'person' data elements from payload to Create Peron

Nexi User can:
-Select a Presented Client from CS
-Search Nexi & Select Client, OR
Select to Create New CS Client  (using IBES Data)

properties.name: Match CP
properties.documentation: Match Applicant to CP.  To match the applicant passed to a known person in Child Support / Hub.

properties.name: >0 Child on Request
properties.documentation: Check to verify there is still at least one child present in the referral before continuing.  If all children were removed due to over age or Emancipated, the referral no longer needs to continue.

properties.name: Resolve Child
properties.documentation: This task automatically sets when Nexi is unable to add a new customer or match the child’s information to an existing customer. SRSs review the information received from IBES to determine whether to add a new customer or match the customer to an existing customer.

properties.name: End Child Request
properties.documentation: This removes this child from the set of people to include in the request from IBES.  The overall request will continue if at least one child remains after all children are matched and checked for Emancipation.

properties.name: Match Children Clients
properties.documentation:
Look for client in different systems (CS, IBES and ICARE), return Client Found, if not client found, continue flow. 

If Match returns more than 1 result, then present resolution task to user. 
If Match returns 1 result, then consider match and move to next step in flow. 
If 0 match returned, then No match found, move to next step in flow.

properties.name: Resolve  Child Outcome
properties.documentation:
The outcome the CS User selects when resolving a Match Person issue.  Outcomes include:
-Create a New Client
-Selecting one option presented by the system (Results in Match Client)
-Searching for an existing Child Support Client and selecting that client (Results in Match Client.)

properties.name: Check Child Status Reason
properties.documentation:
Use Case Search, Search for Child CIN, and Check Child Status. 


To Check the Emancipation Status of a child.  If CS Child Status is Emancipated, Deceased, or Over 18/In School for any case the child is found on, then the Child/Client is considered Emancipated.

properties.name: Existing CS Client Matched
properties.documentation: Match Applicant to Child.  To match the applicant passed to a known person in Child Support / Hub.

properties.name: Check For Duplicate Child
properties.documentation: Checks if the Child is already known to Child Support

properties.name: Match Child(ren)
properties.documentation: Match all children on the referral to known children in Child Support/Hub.  This process checks for Children referred with whom Child Support is unable to take action (over 17.5 or Emancipated) and removes these child(ren) from the referral process.   Process will check ALL children on a specific referral.

properties.name: Resolve Other Parent
properties.documentation: This task automatically sets when Nexi is unable to add a new customer or match the other parent’s information to an existing customer. SRSs review the information received from IBES to determine whether to add a new customer or match the customer to an existing customer.

properties.name: CP and  Child Case Search Outcome
Min Data Known?
properties.documentation:
Check to verify at least 3 of the following elements is known about the NCP/Other Parent:
FName,
LName,
SSN, or 
DOB

AND Gender???

If Not Applicable in IBES, then it will never have enough data.

properties.name: CP and Child Case Search
properties.documentation:
Check for Matching Cases for CP CIN and Child(ren) CIN.  

If there is a matching case, then present that case and the NCP included on that Case as a resolution option 
for the user to Select the NCP (or not).

properties.name: NCP Client Created
properties.documentation: When a Client is matched to one and only one Child Support ClientID.

properties.name: Match NCP Client
properties.documentation:
Look for client in different systems (CS, IBES and ICARE), return Client Found, if not client found, continue flow. 

If Match returns more than 1 result, then present resolution task to user. 
If Match returns 1 result, then consider match and move to next step in flow. 
If 0 match returned, then No match found, move to next step in flow.

properties.name: Check For Duplicate NCP
properties.documentation: Checks if the NCP's CIN/SSN is already known to Child Support

properties.name: Terminate Referral - User Request
properties.documentation: As an SRS worker, I need to be able to end the IBES referral when working Resolve Other Parent task when I find that there is not enough data to continue the flow.

properties.name: New Client with IBES OTHER  Parent Data
User Terminated Referral
properties.documentation: SRS chose to end the entire referral process.

properties.text: Return any case that includes CP CIN and Child(ren) CINs

properties.name: Match NCP
properties.documentation: Match Other Parent / NCP

properties.name: Request Clients Known
properties.documentation: All Clients in request from IBES have CS CIN
